[Student "S"]
{SOUTH would have responded 1\H if EAST had not overcalled. 
But with only 8 points he cannot bid at the 2-level. The Negative Double solves his problem, 
giving this information to partner.

NORTH has good \Hs and enough points to bid game. 
Notice that if EAST had remained silent, SOUTH would have responded 1\H, 
and NORTH would have jumped to game.}

